.net/KovB8NofA9K87RTQJjjdif-360-80.jpg.webp 360w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/KovB8NofA9K87RTQJjjdif-320-80.jpg.webp 320w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 710px) 670px, calc(100vw - 30px)\"/\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/KovB8NofA9K87RTQJjjdif-320-80.jpg\" alt=\"Snow flocked christmas tree\" srcset=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/KovB8NofA9K87RTQJjjdif-1920-80.jpg 1920w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/KovB8NofA9K87RTQJjjdif-1600-80.jpg 1600w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/KovB8NofA9K87RTQJjjdif-1280-80.jpg 1280w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/KovB8NofA9K87RTQJjjdif-1024-80.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/KovB8NofA9K87RTQJjjdif-768-80.jpg 768w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/KovB8NofA9K87RTQJjjdif-415-80.jpg 415w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/KovB8NofA9K87RTQJjjdif-360-80.jpg 360w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/KovB8NofA9K87RTQJjjdif-320-80.jpg 320w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 710px) 670px, calc(100vw - 30px)\" loading=\"lazy\" data-original-mos=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/KovB8NofA9K87RTQJjjdif.jpg\" data-pin-media=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/KovB8NofA9K87RTQJjjdif.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e7ft Half Xmas Snow Flocked Christmas Tree \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis huge 7ft tree has a beautiful frosted effect. It has large, fluffy branches which makes it hard to see it is a half Christmas tree. It\u0026#39;s a great size for apartments or even offices.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eLike all artificial trees, the key to making them look great is by taking the time to fluff them up.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e‘Getting a great-looking tree is also about the effort you put into setting it up. To get your tree looking bigger and more impressive, I would always recommend spending a decent amount of time “fluffing” your tree. This means teasing out each branch and twig so that it reaches its full potential- there really is an art to it!,’ says Mac Harman, CEO of \u003ca data-analytics-id=\"inline-link\" href=\"https://www.balsamhill.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" data-url=\"https://www.balsamhill.co.uk/\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\" data-hl-processed=\"none\"\u003e\u003cu\u003eBalsam Hill\u003c/u\u003e\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigure data-bordeaux-image-check=\"\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ-1920-80.png.webp 1920w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ-1600-80.png.webp 1600w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ-1280-80.png.webp 1280w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ-1024-80.png.webp 1024w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ-768-80.png.webp 768w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ-415-80.png.webp 415w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ-360-80.png.webp 360w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ-320-80.png.webp 320w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 710px) 670px, calc(100vw - 30px)\"/\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ-320-80.png\" alt=\"Half Christmas tree with presents underneath\" srcset=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ-1920-80.png 1920w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ-1600-80.png 1600w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ-1280-80.png 1280w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ-1024-80.png 1024w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ-768-80.png 768w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ-415-80.png 415w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ-360-80.png 360w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ-320-80.png 320w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 710px) 670px, calc(100vw - 30px)\" loading=\"lazy\" data-original-mos=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ.png\" data-pin-media=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/dxjujK8XBsRk8mHdoTvcNQ.png\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e(Image credit: Balsam Hill)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003e‘Starting at the bottom of your tree from the back of each branch (closest to the trunk), stagger each twig and sprig so that it is offset from the one before, pointing in a different direction to those immediately around it.’\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhen the time comes to put together your Christmas decorating ideas, utilise your baubles to give the illusion of a full-size tree.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e‘Position larger baubles to the bottom of the tree as this will give the illusion that your tree has more depth. Add in other sized baubles to the rest of your tree, to create a full and elegant look.’ says Vlatka.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eIf you in need of the extra space this Christmas, you should seriously consider a half Christmas tree - they\u0026#39;re compact whilst maintaing the festive charm you need for the season.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
